      "cooked": "<p>Hello,<br>\nI have an SBike Lite (smart ergometer) from Sportstech. It measures cadence and power independently and displays cadence, watts and km/h on the display und it has 24 resistance levels.<br>\nHowever, I always have to manually adjust the resistance in ERG mode; it doesn\u2019t happen automatically.<br>\nAt first, I thought this might not work in general, but sometimes (about 1 in 20 times) the following happens in slope mode: With each start of a new interval or segment, the resistance on my bike is automatically set to the lowest level.<br>\nSo, Trainerday can apparently change the resistance on my bike, but it doesn\u2019t do so in ERG mode.<br>\nWhat can I do? Thanks in advance for your help.</p>",
